Focusrite Groups Novation Components Application
Google Analytics
Within the Focusrite Groups' Novation Components application we use Google Analytics to track and examine use of the application.
Hotjar
Within the Focusrite Groups' Novation Components application we use Hotjar to track and examine use of the application. Hotjar is also used to display the areas of a page where Users most frequently move the mouse or click. This shows where the points of interest are. These services make it possible to monitor and analyse web traffic and keep track of User behaviour.
Some of these services may record sessions and make them available for later visual playback.
Google Optimize
Within the Focusrite Groups' Novation Components application we use Google Optimize to track and analyze the User response concerning web traffic or behavior regarding changes to the structure, text or any other component of the Novation Components application.
To learn how to prevent tracking in the Novation Components Application click:-
https://support.novationmusic.com/hc/en-gb/articles/360021363080
This processing constitutes:
a Sharing in California
Beta Testing
This type of service makes it possible to manage User access to The Focusrite group, or parts of it, for the purpose of testing a certain feature or the entire Application.
The service provider may automatically collect data related to crashes and statistics related to the User's use of The Focusrite group in a personally identifiable form.
Product design research and Beta testing
By entering the personal information listed below in the webforms of this website or other Focusrite group websites; researchers, consumers and beta testers authorise employees and contractors of the Focusrite Group to use their details to contact them for the purposes of improving the products and services of the Focusrite Group.
Personal Data collected at Sign Up: First Name, Last name, Email address, City, Country, Affiliation to other audio industry companies (if applicable).
Personal Data collected if researcher/Beta tester is selected: Postal address, Phone Number, Skype address, Yammer profile, and their Facebook login or Novation login where applicable.
